Patch Set 2: Code-Review+2

I think this is fine, but I definitely want another opinion, as this changes the behavior of an error message formerly printed on stdout to now being printed on stderr.  On the other hand, some errors are already going to stderr (lines 328 and 346), so this change shouldn't surprise users of this script.
